in particular, is 1.8 million
years old.

00:38.872 --> 00:41.575 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:41.575 --> 00:47.414 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:47.414 --> 01:00.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It began as
Armistice Day, marking the end
of World War I. Now it's
commemorated

01:00.727 --> 01:04.698 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as Veterans Day, honoring all
those who have worn the uniform
of the United States, living

01:04.698 --> 01:07.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and dead.

01:07.200 --> 01:15.809 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, the annual observances
were mixed in with new pledges
of reform. It was a day for

01:15.809 --> 01:20.280 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
keeping with traditions,
including the president laying a
wreath at the Tomb of the
Unknowns

01:20.280 --> 01:27.487 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in Arlington National Cemetery.

01:27.487 --> 01:36.463 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Afterward, Mr. Obama used the
occasion to call for more
progress on speeding up medical

01:36.463 --> 01:41.101 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
services and disability
claims for military veterans.

01:41.101 --> 01:45.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States: If tomorrow,
after the parades and the
ceremonies,

01:45.539 --> 01:51.411 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we roll up the banners and sweep
the veterans halls and go back
to our daily lives forgetting

01:51.411 --> 01:57.651 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the bond between the service of
our veterans and our obligations
as citizens, then we will

01:57.651 --> 02:02.422 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be doing a profound disservice
to our veterans and to the very
cause for which they serve.

02:02.422 --> 02:08.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: At the World War
II Memorial on the National
Mall, former Republican Senator

02:08.362 --> 02:13.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Army veteran Bob Dole paid
his own tribute to those who've
served.

02:13.767 --> 02:21.008 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BOB DOLE, Former U.S. Senator:
It's a day to remember all the
sacrifices made in American

02:21.008 --> 02:27.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
history by people who stood
up for their country.

02:27.514 --> 02:34.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And across the
Atlantic, Britain observed
Remembrance Day with moments of
silence

02:34.454 --> 02:43.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and other somber ceremonies,
while other European nations
marked it as Armistice Day,
honoring

02:43.797 --> 02:48.402 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the millions who lost their
lives during the First World
War.

02:48.402 --> 02:53.273 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Elsewhere, NATO troops in
Afghanistan held observances to
pay tribute to their fallen

02:53.273 --> 02:55.442 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
comrades.

02:55.442 --> 02:58.845 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PADRE COLIN MACLEOD, Chaplain:
So many have lost their lives.
And it would be unforgivable

02:58.845 --> 03:01.782 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of us to forget.

03:01.782 --> 03:07.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: That sentiment
also resonated at Australia's
rain-soaked remembrance ceremony

03:07.654 --> 03:12.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Canberra with Britain's
Prince Charles and his wife in
attendance.

03:12.826 --> 03:18.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: In Myanmar today,
the military-backed government
promised a peaceful transition,

03:18.131 --> 03:23.770 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as the democratic opposition
headed toward a sweeping
election victory. The party led

03:23.770 --> 03:29.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by Aung San Suu Kyi has won the
overwhelming majority of
Parliament races decided since

03:29.476 --> 03:33.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sunday's vote. Her party won a
similar triumph in 1990, but the
military refused to give

03:33.947 --> 03:35.749 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
way.

03:35.749 --> 03:41.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: At least 10,000
people marched in Afghanistan's
capital today, protesting

03:41.388 --> 03:46.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the beheading of seven Shiite
Hazaras. Their bodies were found
in Zabul province on Saturday.

03:46.693 --> 03:49.863 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
One of the victims was a child.

03:49.863 --> 03:55.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, angry demonstrators
carried the coffins through
Kabul, and some tried to force
their

03:55.268 --> 04:00.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
way into the presidential
palace. Police opened fire,
wounding at least 10 people.

04:00.407 --> 04:03.577 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And President Ashraf
Ghani called for calm.

04:03.577 --> 04:07.280 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ASHRAF GHANI, President of
Afghanistan (through
translator): We are committed to
taking revenge

04:07.280 --> 04:12.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for our countrymen's blood. In
this way, we will not spare any
effort. But you have to

04:12.085 --> 04:15.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
remember that anything can
happen if we don't control our
feelings. We should avoid
reactions

04:15.222 --> 04:17.991 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that could result in anarchy.

04:17.991 --> 04:23.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Protesters
demanded that President Ghani
step down if he can't ensure
security.

04:23.430 --> 04:29.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The European Union
pressed African leaders today to
help curb the flow of migrants.

04:29.669 --> 04:33.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The two sides met on Malta,
where the Europeans offered
incentives, as we hear from
Jonathan

04:33.907 --> 04:37.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Rugman of Independent
Television News.

04:37.477 --> 04:43.517 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JONATHAN RUGMAN: Emerging from a
building which once housed
medieval knights tasked

04:43.517 --> 04:50.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with protecting the holy land, a
new champions league, the E.U.'s
leaders still finding their

04:50.390 --> 04:54.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
way in the dark, though, facing
an unprecedented wave of
migration and trying to square
the

04:54.828 --> 04:59.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
circle of helping the desperate
and protecting themselves.

04:59.900 --> 05:05.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their focus tonight is not
Syria, but Africa, with 1.8
billion euros now at the ready
to

05:05.572 --> 05:09.609 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
buy the cooperation of African
leaders, some of it to make sure
migrants turned down for

05:09.609 --> 05:14.014 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
asylum really do go home.

05:14.014 --> 05:19.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Africans account for 14 percent
of this year's arrival. But it's
much further east off Turkey

05:19.753 --> 05:25.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
