coming, 6,000 people reaching
Greece every day. It's thought

05:25.859 --> 05:31.598 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a trafficker dived off this
dinghy this morning, no doubt
hoping to cash in on the next.

05:31.598 --> 05:37.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back in Malta, you need a ladder
to reach the uppermost files of
asylum seekers. And

05:37.337 --> 05:42.442 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the more new arrivals, the more
the tide is beginning to turn,
many in Germany are ruing

05:42.442 --> 05:48.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the day Angela Merkel flung her
country's door wide open, the
Greeks not prepared to

05:48.415 --> 05:55.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
take back those who arrived
there first, and African leaders
demanding more visas so Africans

05:55.689 --> 06:01.928 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
can visit Europe legally, rather
than risking their lives to get
here instead.

06:01.928 --> 06:08.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Back in this
country, a Missouri man is in
jail, suspected of posting
online

06:08.001 --> 06:13.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
