debate shifted from personality
to policy.

07:42.429 --> 07:45.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The candidates used their fourth
face-off to better define their
differences.

07:45.932 --> 07:52.839 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The topics ranged from
the economy and taxes.

07:52.839 --> 07:56.576 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SEN. RAND PAUL (R-KY),
Presidential Candidate: I want a
government really, really small,

07:56.576 --> 07:59.846 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
so small you can barely see it.

07:59.846 --> 08:03.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: You wouldn't favor
breaking up the big banks? You
think they're big enough,
they're

08:03.883 --> 08:07.854 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
OK as they are, as
big as they are?

08:07.854 --> 08:10.023 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEN CARSON (R), Presidential
Candidate: I would have policies
that wouldn't allow that

08:10.023 --> 08:10.957 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to occur.

08:10.957 --> 08:13.660 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: To
international affairs.

08:13.660 --> 08:19.599 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SEN. MARCO RUBIO (R-FL),
Presidential Candidate: I know
that Rand is a committed
isolationist.

08:19.599 --> 08:28.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
