great Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, an
Arthur Conan Doyle devotee

39:24.562 --> 39:29.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who says he applied Holmesian
deduction and reasoning while he
was playing pro ball.

39:29.033 --> 39:31.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He recently talked with Jeffrey
Brown here in Washington.

39:31.869 --> 39:34.639 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Kareem
Abdul-Jabbar, welcome to you.

39:34.639 --> 39:36.307 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR, Author,
"Mycroft Holmes": Well, thank
you so much.

39:36.307 --> 39:39.344 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's interesting.
Reading this book, you're taking
one fiction, right, the

39:39.344 --> 39:42.413 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sherlock Holmes books, and
creating another, a new one.

39:42.413 --> 39:43.648 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR: Yes.

39:43.648 --> 39:45.516 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Tell me how you
thought about it. What you were
doing?

39:45.516 --> 39:50.755 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR: Mycroft has
never been really explored as a
subject.

39:50.755 --> 39:57.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he's the one person in all
of these stories that is the
closest to Sherlock. So I was

39:57.562 --> 39:59.931 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
just curious about him.

39:59.931 --> 40:02.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He's the older
and even by Sherlock's terms the
smarter brother. Right?

40:02.734 --> 40:03.735 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR: The
smarter brother, yes.

40:03.735 --> 40:05.136 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But we don't
know that much about him.

40:05.136 --> 40:07.772 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You had fun filling
in the character.

40:07.772 --> 40:12.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR: Filling in
his backstory and how he got to
be who he was, because by

40:12.310 --> 40:17.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the time he's in the Sherlock
Holmes stories, he's
middle-aged, overweight, and
just really

40:17.548 --> 40:21.352 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
has withdrawn from the world.

40:21.352 --> 40:27.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He only goes to his offices, his
club and his apartment. And he
doesn't go any other

40:27.859 --> 40:32.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
place. We wanted to explain how
he got to be like that, because,
probably, as a younger

40:32.330 --> 40:36.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
man, he probably had a
much different life.

40:36.067 --> 40:39.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In filling in the
story, though, you get to look
at a lot of bigger issues,

40:39.137 --> 40:41.673 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because you're seeing Britain
as a colonial power.

40:41.673 --> 40:43.141 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KAREEM ABDUL-JABBAR: Yes.

40:43.141 --> 40:49.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You're taking us
to Trinidad. The Dr. Watson
character is a black man, so

40:49.247 --> 40:53.251 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
